%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Welspun%20Enterprises%20Q2FY25%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20falls%2011%25%20to%20Rs%2061.56%20crore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730281655000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fwelspun-enterprises-q2-results-net-profit-falls-11-to-rs-61-56-cr-124103000736_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Total%20income%20rose%20to%20Rs%20837.92%20crore%20from%20Rs%20692.65%20crore%20in%20the%20year-ago%20period.%20Expenses%20surged%20to%20Rs%20736.33%20crore%20from%20Rs%20595.61%20crore%20a%20year%20ago%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Millennials%20are%20turning%2040%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20and%20it's%20freaking%20them%20out%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20%26quot%3B40%26quot%3B%20candle%20in%20avocado%20toast%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67213c889b3250dbbceae7be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEverybody%20is%20at%20least%20a%20little%20scared%20of%20turning%2040.%20Well%2C%20maybe%20not%20%3Cem%3Eeverybody%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20but%20the%20conventional%20wisdom%20is%20that%20many%20people%20stare%20down%20their%20fifth%20decade%20with%20a%20touch%20of%20dread.%20Reaching%20a%20new%20decade%20is%20always%20weird.%20Turning%2030%20says%20%26quot%3Badult.%26quot%3B%20Hitting%2050%20means%20you're%20officially%20AARP-eligible.%20At%2040%2C%20it's%20%3Cem%3Eso%20%3C%2Fem%3Eover.%20You're%20middle-aged%2C%20and%20the%20wear%20and%20tear%20of%20life%20is%20almost%20certainly%20taking%20its%20toll%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20faithful%20you've%20been%20to%20your%20strict%20skincare%20regimen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20millennials%20approach%20the%20milestone%2C%20things%20look%20a%20bit%20different%20than%20they%20did%20when%20our%20baby-boomer%20parents%20reached%20it%20and%20declared%20themselves%20%26quot%3Bover%20the%20hill.%26quot%3B%20(I'm%20a%20millennial%2C%20so%20I'm%20using%20%26quot%3Bour%26quot%3B%20here.)%20Forty%20is%20supposedly%20the%20new%2030.%20The%20start%20of%20middle%20age%20no%20longer%20means%20sending%20your%20kids%20off%20to%20college%2C%20getting%20a%20divorce%2C%20or%20buying%20yourself%20a%20Corvette.%20The%20modern%2040%20means%20having%20toddlers%20running%20around%2C%20buying%20your%20first%20home%2C%20and%2C%20at%20last%2C%20catching%20up%20on%20retirement%20savings.%20Or%20looking%20around%20and%20wondering%20whether%20some%20of%20those%20life%20touchpoints%20passed%20you%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThings%20happen%20in%20midlife%20that%20you%20may%20not%20be%20prepared%20for.%20One%20is%20simply%20that%20aspirations%20align%20with%20reality%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Carol%20Graham%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20in%20economic%20studies%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%20who%20has%20studied%20happiness%20(and%20unhappiness)%20and%20aging.%20%26quot%3BBy%20the%20time%20you're%2040%2C%2045%2C%20you%20can't%20sing%2C%20and%20you%20can't%20play%20guitar%3B%20maybe%20it's%20time%20to%20give%20up%20on%20your%20aspirations%20of%20being%20a%20rock%20star.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20you're%20prepared%20for%20it%20or%20not%2C%2040%20hits%20differently%20%E2%80%94%20culturally%2C%20physically%2C%20emotionally.%20You%20find%20yourself%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsandwich-generation-mom-balance-child-care-eldercare-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20%26quot%3Bsandwich%26quot%3B%20phase%20of%20life%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20managing%20care%20for%20your%20children%20and%20your%20parents%20in%20a%20body%20that%2C%20as%20much%20as%20you%20hate%20to%20admit%20it%2C%20doesn't%20work%20as%20well%20as%20it%20used%20to.%20Suddenly%2C%20everyone%20around%20you%20is%20talking%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20weightlifting%2C%20lest%20you%20fall%20apart%2C%20and%20debating%20whether%20to%20keep%20up%20the%20dye%20job%20or%20give%20up%20the%20game%20on%20the%20grays.%20For%20women%2C%20fertility%20is%20waning%2C%20and%20menopause%20is%20on%20the%20horizon.%20Is%20that%203%20a.m.%20insomnia%20the%20result%20of%20stress%20about%20your%20kid's%20report%20card%2C%20a%20classic%20case%20of%20existential%20dread%2C%20or%20a%20symptom%20of%20perimenopause%3F%20At%20work%2C%20you%20realize%20you're%20protected%20from%20age%20discrimination%2C%20which%20you%20feel%20like%20you're%20still%20much%20too%20young%20for.%20But%20now%20that%20you%20think%20of%20it%2C%20you%20did%20take%20your%20graduation%20date%20off%20your%20LinkedIn%20profile%20a%20while%20back.%20It%20just%20seemed%20like%20a%20good%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForty%20is%20an%20arbitrary%20number%2C%20and%20there's%20nothing%20%3Cem%3Eparticularly%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehorrifying%20about%20it.%20Nevertheless%2C%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20it's%20terrifying.%20And%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-socks-jeans-brands-aging-cash-advertising-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20generation%20that%20once%20embodied%20youth%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20knocking%20at%2040's%20door%2C%20if%20they're%20not%20there%20already.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%2040%20seems%20daunting%3A%20The%20decade%20of%20life%20ahead%20is%2C%20scientifically%20speaking%2C%20supposed%20to%20be%20miserable.%20Academic%20literature%20on%20happiness%20generally%20suggests%20that%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs00148-020-00797-z%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esatisfaction%20with%20life%20as%20we%20age%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F08%2Fglobal_20160825_happiness_stress_age.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EU-shaped%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20we're%20young%2C%20we're%20happy%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20that%20declines%2C%20bottoming%20out%20in%20middle%20age%2C%20about%2040%20to%2050.%20(The%20low%20point%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw26641%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E47.2%3C%2Fa%3E.)%20As%20we%20pass%20middle%20age%20and%20get%20older%2C%20we%20get%20happier%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHannes%20Schwandt%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20human%20development%20and%20social%20policy%20at%20Northwestern%20University%2C%20told%20me%20that%20midlife%20nadir%20is%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bbiological%20regularity%20comparable%20to%20a%20second%20puberty.%26quot%3B%20It's%20caused%20by%20unmet%20expectations%20and%20aspirations%20that%20are%20painful%20in%20midlife%20but%2C%20as%20his%20research%20has%20found%2C%20%26quot%3Bbeneficially%20abandoned%20and%20experienced%20with%20less%20regret%20during%20old%20age.%26quot%3B%20Basically%2C%20your%2040s%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bthis%20is%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20vibe%20that%20can%20be%20upsetting%20but%20that%20fades%20as%20you%20get%20older%2C%20accept%20things%2C%20grow%20to%20appreciate%20your%20relationships%20and%20experience%2C%20and%20get%20back%20some%20independence%20as%20your%20children%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20young%2C%20you%20are%20typically%20overestimating%20what%20you're%20getting%20in%20the%20future.%20When%20you%20get%20married%2C%20you%20think%20that%20your%20marriage%20will%20last%3B%20you%20don't%20think%20that%20there's%20a%2030%25%20chance%20you'll%20be%20the%20one%20that%20is%20divorced%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNot%20everything%20turns%20out%20as%20nicely%2C%20and%20this%20can%20then%20be%20just%20accumulating%20disappointment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwandt%20added%20that%20disappointment%20leads%20people%20to%20revise%20their%20expectations%20and%20have%20a%20less%20rosy%20outlook%20about%20the%20future%2C%20so%20they%20land%20in%20%26quot%3Bdouble%20misery%26quot%3B%20territory.%20The%20good%20news%20is%20that%20it%20gets%20better.%20The%20bad%20news%20is%20that%20it%20takes%20time%20to%20figure%20that%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20were%20born%20from%201981%20to%201996%2C%20so%20everyone%20in%20the%20'81-to-'84%20range%20%E2%80%94%20millions%20of%20members%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurant-job-gains-march-millennials-dining-out-avocado-toast-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bavocado%20toast%26quot%3B%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20has%20hit%2040%20or%20is%20about%20to%20in%20the%20next%20couple%20of%20months.%20Millions%20more%20will%20do%20so%20over%20the%20next%20decade.%20Many%20are%20turning%2040%20having%20only%20recently%20reached%20typical%20adult%20milestones%2C%20or%20having%20accomplished%20less%20than%20they%20might%20have%20expected.%20The%20delays%20mean%20the%20%26quot%3Bhuh%3F%26quot%3B%20aspect%20that%20comes%20with%20the%20start%20of%20middle%20age%20has%20been%20redefined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20getting%20married%20later%20and%20having%20their%20kids%20later%20and%20settling%20into%20careers%20later%2C%20and%20so%20they%20may%20be%20thinking%2C%20'Man%2C%20when%20my%20parents%20were%2040%2C%20they'd%20already%20been%20married%20for%2015%20years%20and%20had%20completed%20their%20family%20and%20been%20working%20in%20a%20career%20for%2020%20years%2C%20and%20that's%20just%20not%20where%20I%20am%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Jean%20Twenge%2C%20a%20psychologist%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BGenerations%3A%20The%20Real%20Differences%20Between%20Gen%20Z%2C%20Millennials%2C%20Gen%20X%2C%20Boomers%2C%20and%20Silents%20%E2%80%94%20and%20What%20They%20Mean%20for%20America's%20Future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDelayed%20development%20isn't%20all%20bad%20%E2%80%94%20having%20kids%20later%20in%20life%20when%20you're%20more%20established%20in%20your%20career%20might%20remove%20some%20financial%20stress%2C%20for%20example.%20Millennials%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20Gen%20Xers%20and%20baby%20boomers%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2019%2F02%2F14%2Fmillennial-life-how-young-adulthood-today-compares-with-prior-generations-2%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAmong%2520Millennials%252C%2520around%2520four%252Din%2Cthey%2520were%2520the%2520same%2520age.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20college%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%2C%20despite%20the%20stereotype%2C%20they're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fpodcasts%2Fgoogle-news-update%2Fmillennials-are-now-wealthier-than-generations-before-at-the-same-age%2Ff2aff5e1-ff70-4b34-99c8-1e7a9927d3cb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewealthier%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20prior%20generations%20were%20at%20the%20same%20age.%20Life%20expectancies%20have%20increased%20from%20where%20they%20were%20decades%20ago%2C%20so%2040%20isn't%20as%20%26quot%3Bmiddle-aged%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20used%20to%20be%20(or%20at%20least%20that's%20what%20I'd%20like%20to%20tell%20myself).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwandt%20is%2042%20and%20the%20parent%20of%20two%20young%20children%20himself.%20He%20posited%20that%20delayed%20development%20might%20actually%20ease%20some%20of%20the%20midlife%20crisis%2C%20or%20at%20least%20put%20it%20off%2C%20because%20people%20simply%20don't%20have%20the%20space%20to%20sit%20back%20and%20reflect%20and%20wonder%20what%20might%20have%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20many%20worries%20and%20many%20issues%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20even%20have%20time%20to%20think%20about%20those%20questions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20things%20settle%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20the%20dust%20settles%2C%20then%20you%20think%2C%20'Hey%2C%20what%20am%20I%20doing%3F%20Where%20am%20I%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20upside%20is%20that%20as%20you%20get%20older%2C%20you%20become%20wiser%20and%20better%20able%20to%20handle%20life%20hiccups.%20What%20felt%20like%20a%20disaster%20at%2020%20does%20not%20feel%20that%20way%20at%2045%20%E2%80%94%20you%20understand%20that%20this%2C%20too%2C%20shall%20pass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20the%20time%20you%20get%20older%2C%20you've%20gone%20through%20a%20lot%20of%20bad%20experiences%2C%20and%20they're%20not%20always%20pleasant%2C%20but%20unless%20you%20get%20really%20ill%20and%20die%20or%20you%20have%20a%20really%20horrible%20shock%2C%20you%20realize%20you%20can%20get%20over%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Balik%2C%2036%2C%20a%20climate-policy%20director%20in%20New%20Jersey%2C%20told%20me%20that%20one%20thing%20that%20freaks%20him%20out%20about%20staring%20down%2040%20is%20seeing%20his%20first%20gray%20hairs%2C%20an%20experience%20he%20finds%20%26quot%3Ba%20little%20bit%20terrifying.%26quot%3B%20Bigger%20picture%2C%20it's%20been%20jarring%20to%20realize%20there%20aren't%20really%20adults%20in%20the%20room%20to%20fix%20everything%20%E2%80%94%20behind%20the%20curtain%2C%20the%20Wizard%20of%20Oz%20is%20just%20another%20uncertain%20person%20trying%20to%20figure%20it%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20younger%2C%20you%20assume%20that%20there%20are%20people%20that%20are%20smarter%20than%20you%20and%20that%20have%20figured%20it%20all%20out%20and%20are%20working%20on%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20turns%20out%20that%20it's%20just%20up%20to%20all%20of%20us%2C%20collectively.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EKelly%2C%20a%2039-year-old%20fundraiser%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20has%20been%20doing%20a%20lot%20of%20reflecting%20ahead%20of%20her%2040th%20birthday.%20She's%20been%20journaling%20about%20it%2C%20talking%20to%20her%20therapist%20about%20it%2C%20and%20reading%20%26quot%3BAll%20Fours%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20book%20about%20a%20woman%20in%20her%2040s.%20She's%20not%20so%20worried%20about%20her%20fertility%20%E2%80%94%20she%20has%20a%20son%2C%20and%20she's%20a%20one-and-done%20mom%20%E2%80%94%20but%20she's%20aware%20that%20her%20body%20is%20changing%2C%20as%20is%2C%20maybe%2C%20her%20place%20in%20society.%20There%20aren't%20a%20ton%20of%20great%20examples%20in%20popular%20culture%20of%20what%20her%2040s%20are%20supposed%20to%20look%20like%20%E2%80%94%20the%20movie%20%26quot%3BThis%20Is%2040%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20supposes%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BFather%20of%20the%20Bride%2C%26quot%3B%20maybe.%20She%20remembers%20the%20stupid%20%26quot%3Bover%20the%20hill%26quot%3B%20birthday%20cards%20her%20parents%20got%20when%20they%20hit%20the%20milestone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20I'm%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20something%2C%20and%2040%20is%20that%20cultural%20touchpoint%20for%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20told%20me.%20She%20asked%20for%20her%20last%20name%20to%20be%20withheld%20to%20protect%20her%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20anxieties%20about%20turning%2040%20aren't%20unique%2C%20but%20Kelly%20can't%20help%20but%20wonder%20if%20she%20would%20feel%20better%20about%20it%20had%20the%20pandemic%20not%20happened%2C%20with%20the%20associated%20lockdowns%20and%20workforce%20upheaval%20and%20inflation.%20It%20stole%20the%20end%20of%20her%20youth.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20get%20to%20just%20gradually%20and%20gracefully%20move%20into%20midlife%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20bit%20of%20the%20arrested%20development%20that%20kind%20of%20came%20from%20this%20extenuating%20circumstance%20and%20not%20this%20internal%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20be%20remiss%20not%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20the%20experience%20of%2040%20is%20different%20for%20women%20than%20it%20is%20for%20men.%20It's%20not%20just%20that%20things%20change%20physically%20for%20women%20as%20they%20get%20older%20%E2%80%94%20they%20change%20culturally%2C%20too.%20We%20put%20a%20premium%20on%20youth%20and%20beauty%2C%20especially%20for%20women%2C%20and%20as%20they%20age%2C%20many%20feel%20like%20they're%20treated%20as%20invisible.%20The%20antiaging%20industry%20targets%20all%20genders%2C%20but%20it's%20mostly%20women%20who%20get%20told%20how%20to%20stay%20young.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelly%20is%20lucky%20that%20in%20her%20field%20of%20work%2C%20being%20a%20little%20older%20is%20a%20bonus.%20She%20has%20friends%20who%20work%20in%20tech%20%E2%80%94%20a%20youth-oriented%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-ageism-tech-jobs-gen-z-boomers-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20are%20struggling%20to%20find%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They're%20not%20making%20it%20past%20interview%20rounds%20they're%20sure%20they%20would%20have%20flown%20through%20five%20years%20ago.%20Maybe%20that's%20attributable%20to%20a%20tech-industry%20hiring%20slowdown%2C%20but%20they%20wonder%20if%20it's%20their%20age.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20actually%20having%20a%20lot%20of%20those%20conversations%20about%20how%20you%20have%20to%20kind%20of%20remove%20years%20from%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20don't%20put%20your%20graduation%20date%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internet%2C%20too%2C%20gives%20aging%20nowadays%20a%20different%20flavor.%20TikTok%20and%20Instagram%20put%20generational%20debates%20front%20and%20center%2C%20with%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20jousting%20over%20hair%20parts%20and%20sock%20lengths%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-was-right-to-mock-these-millennial-style-trends-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejeans%20widths%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We're%20also%20staring%20at%20our%20aging%20faces%20a%20lot%20more%20thanks%20to%20Zoom%20and%20the%20ubiquity%20of%20cameras%20in%20our%20lives.%20It%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20compare%20ourselves%20to%20one%20another.%20The%20question%20isn't%20just%20whether%20my%2040%20will%20look%20like%20my%20parents'%2040%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20also%20whether%20it%20will%20look%20like%20the%2040%20of%20everyone%20from%20my%20high%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20you're%20comparing%20your%2040%20to%20your%20quote-unquote%20friends'%2040%20online%20through%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%20and%20Snapchat%2C%20whatever%20it%20may%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lindsey%20Anderson%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Maryland%20who%20studies%20aging.%20You're%20also%20aware%20they're%20looking%20at%20you.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20that%20there's%20also%20this%20increased%2C%20maybe%2C%20feeling%20that%20if%20you%20fail%20in%20some%20way%2C%20people%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20very%20visible%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAlso%2C%20I%20mean%20'fail'%20very%20much%20in%20quotations%2C%20because%20what%20failure%20is%20is%20really%20subjective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAging%20means%20moving%20out%20of%20that%20coveted%2018-to-34%20demographic%20that%20culturally%20sets%20the%20tone%20on%20what's%20cool.%20There's%20also%20no%20way%20to%20sugarcoat%20the%20fact%20that%20part%20of%20aging%20is%20decline%2C%20decay%2C%20and%2C%20eventually%2C%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20around%2040%20isn't%20all%20doom%20and%20gloom%20for%20millennials.%20Because%20life%20expectancy%20is%20longer%20and%20people%20are%20taking%20their%20time%20in%20getting%20around%20to%20%26quot%3Badulting%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20story%20of%20the%2040s%20is%20one%20of%20extended%20youth%20more%20than%20a%20transition%20into%20old%20age.%20People%20take%20better%20care%20of%20themselves%20these%20days%20than%20they%20did%2C%20say%2C%2050%20years%20ago%2C%20so%20while%20you%20can't%20turn%20back%20the%20clock%2C%20those%20years%20of%20slathering%20on%20sunscreen%20do%20pay%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20important%20to%20remember%20that%2040%20is%20a%20random%20number%2C%20Anderson%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20all%20arbitrary%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20age%20differently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20experience%20the%20middle-age%20dip%20in%20happiness%20differently%2C%20too.%20Those%20who%20tend%20to%20have%20a%20more%20positive%20disposition%20generally%20have%20a%20smoother%20go%20of%20it.%20Graham%2C%20from%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20told%20me%20that%20the%20U-curve%20story%20might%20be%20changing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20some%20reasons%20that%20are%20quite%20disturbing.%20It's%20not%20that%20midlife%20has%20gotten%20easier%20(sorry%2C%20millennials)%20but%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fsociety%2F2024%2Fmar%2F20%2Fyoung-people-becoming-less-happy-than-older-generations-research-shows%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyoung%20people%20are%20unhappier%3C%2Fa%3E%20now%2C%20too%20(really%20sorry%2C%20Gen%20Z).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20much%20harder%20to%20even%20think%20about%20what%20is%20going%20on%20in%20terms%20of%20youth%20unhappiness%20now%2C%20but%20it's%20to%20the%20point%20that%20they%20don't%20start%20higher.%20So%20it's%20not%20really%20great.%20In%20fact%2C%20they%20may%20be%20happier%20in%20midlife%20than%20they%20are%20as%20youth%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20easy%20explanations%20like%20social%20media%20or%20COVID%20%E2%80%94%20they%20exacerbated%20something%20deeper%20going%20on%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20we%20have%20a%20full%20handle%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20whether%20today's%20young%20people%20will%20buck%20the%20trend%20and%20become%20happier%20as%20they%20age%20or%20become%20even%20unhappier.%20Turning%2040%20could%20be%20worse%20for%20Gen%20Zers%20than%20it%20is%20for%20millennials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20little%20too%20close%20to%2040%20for%20comfort%2C%20and%20I%20was%20hoping%20this%20story%20would%20make%20me%20feel%20better.%20It%20did%2C%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20in%20that%20at%20least%20I'm%20(probably)%20going%20to%20get%20there%2C%20and%20I%20have%20really%20been%20good%20about%20sunscreen.%20Plus%2C%20after%20that%20midlife%20dip%2C%20things%20get%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20fun%20again%20later%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-middle-age-40-savings-careers-kids-boomers-gen-z-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730281621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67213caa9b3250dbbceae7fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-middle-age-40-savings-careers-kids-boomers-gen-z-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Millennials%2C%20a%20generation%20defined%20by%20their%20youth%2C%20are%20no%20longer%20young.%20That's%20causing%20many%20of%20them%20to%20reevaluate%20their%20lives.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-middle-age-40-savings-careers-kids-boomers-gen-z-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IBBI%2C%20IBA%20to%20launch%20centralised%20platform%20for%20asset%20liquidation%20auctions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730281256000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fnews%2Fibbi-iba-to-launch-centralised-platform-for-liquidation-asset-auctions-124103000738_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Initially%2C%20the%20platform%20will%20be%20deployed%20in%20pilot%20mode%2C%20with%20a%20full%20rollout%20planned%20at%20a%20later%20date%20after%20incorporating%20improvements%20based%20on%20usage%20feedback%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canoni