%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20kicked%20things%20off%20with%20high-quality%20free%20food%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20It%20now%20has%20dozens%20of%20cafes%20at%20the%20Googleplex%20in%20Mountain%20View%20and%20in%20offices%20around%20the%20world%20offering%20an%20array%20of%20free%20meals%20cooked%20by%20chefs%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-of-jamie-olivers-top-chefs-is-now-working-for-google-2016-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efine-dining%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20gathered%20pace%20from%20there%20as%20Facebook%20and%20other%20emerging%20tech%20giants%20began%20competing%20hard%20for%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerks%20became%20so%20expected%20that%20such%20benefits%20stopped%20being%20highlighted%20in%20job%20postings%20across%20the%20sector%2C%20according%20to%20Allison%20Shrivastava%2C%20associate%20economist%20at%20Indeed's%20Hiring%20Lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221330d176-8353-4d90-b415-2e0c1403bb0c%5C%22%3EHacking%20the%20perk%20system%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20culture%20of%20moving%20fast%20and%20breaking%20things%2C%20it%20was%20perhaps%20inevitable%20some%20staffers%20hacked%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Meta%20banned%20employees%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hcamag.com%2Fus%2Fspecialization%2Fbenefits%2Ffacebooks-parent-company-meta-cutting-perks-for-employees%2F399035%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebringing%20in%20Tupperware%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20too%20many%20had%20been%20stocking%20up%20on%20free%20food%20and%20taking%20it%20home%20with%20them.%20Even%20then%2C%20employees%20invented%20workarounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20got%20clued%20up%20on%20people%20taking%20food%20home%2C%20so%20people%20would%20start%20bringing%20their%20family%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20for%20meals%20on%20campus%2C%20said%20a%20former%20Google%20employee%2C%20who%20worked%20at%20the%20company%20for%20five%20years.%20(Google's%20policy%20also%20states%20that%20employees%20can't%20take%20food%20from%20its%20cafeteria%20home.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Grubgate%20episode%20from%20earlier%20in%20October%2C%20Meta%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-fires-employees-abusing-grubhub-meal-credit-perk-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efired%3C%2Fa%3E%20several%20employees%20after%20they%20misused%20Grubhub%20vouchers%20to%20order%20nonfood%20items%20like%20laundry%20detergent%2C%20acne%20pads%2C%20and%20wine%20glasses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFood%20isn't%20the%20only%20in-house%20luxury%20where%20employees%20tested%20the%20boundaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20used%20the%20laundry%20expense%20%E2%80%94%20yes%2C%20do%20my%20own%20clothing%2C%20but%20also%20my%20spouse's%20clothing.%20It's%20one%20big%20laundry%20hamper%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day.%20Am%20I%20supposed%20to%20use%20it%20for%20my%20spouse's%20laundry%3F%20I%20don't%20know%2C%20but%20that%20kind%20of%20thing%20seems%20very%20minor%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20former%20US%20Meta%20employee%20who%20was%20offered%20a%20clothes-washing%20credit%20because%20they%20worked%20at%20an%20office%20with%20no%20on-site%20laundry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20briefly%20nixed%20its%20in-house%20laundry%20service%20in%202023%20before%20reinstating%20it%20%E2%80%94%20though%20it's%20now%20no%20longer%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20voucher-based%20perks%20was%20long%20established%20at%20tech%20companies%20with%20offices%20that%20couldn't%20cater%20for%20food%20and%20other%20services.%20These%20sorts%20of%20benefits%20ballooned%20during%20the%20COVID-induced%20work-from-home%20era%20as%20employers%20looked%20to%20maintain%20employee%20morale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20at%20Snap%2C%20the%20company%20used%20to%20offer%20employees%20Snapchat-yellow-branded%20cash%20cards%20loaded%20with%20an%20allowance%20for%20a%20daily%20meal.%20%26quot%3BIt%20could%20be%20used%20anywhere%20%E2%80%94%20so%20yes%2C%20people%20used%20to%20save%20it%20up%20during%20the%20week%20and%20blow%20it%20on%20a%20big%20shop%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20former%20Snap%20UK%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226075ba1e-765c-46ab-ac39-f94ef3ba98c6%5C%22%3EA%20%242%2C600%20travel%20pass%20ruse%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20Meta%20employee%20who%20left%20last%20year%20recalls%20former%20colleagues%20claiming%20a%20%242%2C600%20annual%20travel%20pass%20to%20get%20the%20receipt%20to%20expense%2C%20only%20to%20then%20instantly%20refund%20their%20tickets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%243%2C000%20a%20year%20%26quot%3Bwellness%20stipend%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20meant%20to%20cover%20costs%20for%20employees'%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%20and%20care%20for%20their%20families%20%E2%80%94%20was%20exchanged%20for%20Nintendo%20Switch%20consoles%20by%20other%20staffers%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%2425-a-month%20advertising%20credit%20given%20to%20employees%20to%20test%20and%20improve%20their%20skills%20on%20Facebook%20Ad%20Manager%20was%20instead%20sold%20for%20%2420%20cash%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20kind%20of%20normal.%20Oh%2C%20you're%20getting%20an%20Uber%20Eats%2C%20you%20throw%20stuff%20in.%20It%20wasn't%20like%20you%20felt%20you%20were%20cheating%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20former%20Instagram%20employee.%20%26quot%3BYou%20feel%20like%20that's%20your%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dff5050e-64c2-453b-801c-91a664734b08%5C%22%3EA%20growing%20sense%20of%20entitlement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20say%20that%20all%20this%20pampering%20of%20tech%20employees%20led%20to%20a%20growing%20sense%20of%20entitlement%2C%20which%20allowed%20some%20to%20think%20they%20could%20push%20the%20limits%20of%20what%20was%20acceptable%20when%20it%20came%20to%20perks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoogle%20would%20give%20out%20Christmas%20presents%2C%20the%20latest%20phone%20or%20something%2C%20and%20I%20would%20see%20people%20complain%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20Googler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F23277797%2Fmark-zuckerberg-meta-facebook-employees-pressure%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%20famously%20bristled%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20an%20all-hands%20meeting%20about%20coming%20layoffs%20in%202022%20when%20an%20employee%20asked%20whether%20the%20company%20would%20continue%20its%20COVID-era%20bonus%20holidays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20would%20get%20angry%20about%20the%20littlest%20of%20things%20in%20the%20live%20comments%20when%20Zuck%20did%20the%20company%20all-hands%20%E2%80%94%20the%20kinds%20of%20comments%20that%20would%20get%20you%20fired%20in%20any%20other%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20former%20Meta%20employee%20who%20left%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3B'How%20can%20you%20cut%20the%20laundry%20benefit%3F'%20'The%20food%20is%20crap%20now!'%20etc.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22affcf9d4-8854-4d15-8c10-dfcd74cce30f%5C%22%3EWhere%20to%20draw%20the%20line%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20tech%20workers%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20endorsed%20expense%20fraud.%20Indeed%2C%20there%20are%20tax%20consequences%20for%20companies%20and%20individuals%20if%20tax-exempted%20benefits%20or%20vouchers%20or%20a%20specific%20purpose%20are%20used%20for%20something%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20tech%20workers%20told%20BI%20that%20companies%20never%20really%20made%20it%20clear%20what%20was%20acceptable.%20Is%20it%20ok%20if%20your%20partner%20stops%20by%20late%20to%20see%20you%20in%20the%20office%20and%20grabs%20a%20French%20fry%20from%20a%20plate%20of%20food%20that%20your%20employer%20paid%20for%3F%20What%20about%2010%20fries%2C%20or%20a%20whole%20plate%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Mork%2C%20who%20led%20marketing%20for%20Google%20Play%20before%20leaving%20in%202013%2C%20thinks%20tech%20companies%20have%20moved%20too%20far%20away%20from%20their%20initial%20worker-friendly%20cultures%20as%20their%20focus%20has%20turned%20toward%20Wall%20Street's%20profit%20expectations.%20That%20shift%20has%20eroded%20leadership%20skills%2C%20meaning%20some%20employees%20aren't%20clear%20on%20their%20company's%20values%20and%20rules%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployers%20don't%20focus%20on%20anything%20that's%20not%20being%20measured%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what's%20not%20being%20measured%20is%20culture%2C%20leadership%2C%20and%20values%2C%26quot%3B%20Mork%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDilip%20Rao%2C%20CEO%20of%20Sharebite%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20lets%20client%20companies%20give%20workers%20credit%20cards%20for%20meals%20that%20only%20work%20at%20approved%20restaurants%2C%20criticized%20companies%20for%20offering%20easily%20abusable%20perks%20to%20workers%20then%20penalizing%20them%20for%20it.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20even%20put%20somebody%20in%20that%20position%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrubgate%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20perfect%20example%20of%20a%20recurring%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BObviously%20it's%20gained%20visibility%20because%20it%20happened%20at%20Meta.%20But%20I%20got%20to%20tell%20you%2C%20this%20same%20exact%20problem%20happens%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he's%20seen%20other%20examples%20of%20tech%20employees%20using%20company%20meal%20vouchers%20to%20buy%20firewood%20and%20pet%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225abf862f-fe39-4e31-a101-ebe4603f8f26%5C%22%3ELayoffs%20led%20to%20more%20perks-grifting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELayoffs%20across%20the%20industry%20have%20left%20some%20employees%20cynical%20about%20the%20companies%20they%20work%20at%2C%20and%20worried%20about%20job%20security.%20When%20you%20might%20be%20let%20go%20by%20a%20company%2C%20you%20might%20max%20out%20on%20perks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20job%20marketplace%20Trueup%2C%20at%20least%20650%2C000%20tech%20workers%20have%20been%20cut%20since%20the%20start%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20the%20layoffs%20started%2C%20people%20were%20focused%20on%20spending%20whatever%20perks%20they%20had%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20former%20Meta%20employee%20who%20left%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20there%20may%20be%20fewer%20perks-grifting%20opportunities.%20Alongside%20industrywide%20layoffs%20that%20began%20in%202022%2C%20many%20tech%20companies%20also%20trimmed%20back%20the%20benefits%20on%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Big%20Tech%20pampering%20era%20could%20soon%20be%20over%2C%20according%20to%20Bruce%20Daisley%2C%20a%20former%20vice%20president%20at%20Twitter%20and%20YouTube%20who%20now%20coaches%20leadership%20teams%20at%20large%20companies%20on%20workplace%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20feeling%20that%20it%20became%20a%20monster%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20killed%2C%26quot%3B%20Daisley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-workers-pushed-limits-of-perks-benefits-pampering-over-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730278801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67214791a0a0cc14f224c612%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-workers-pushed-limits-of-perks-benefits-pampering-over-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Meta's%20'Grubhubgate'%20speaks%20to%20a%20bigger%20culture%20shift%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20festering%20distrust%20between%20employers%20and%20employees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22loreilly%40insider.com%20(Lara%20O'Reilly%2CRob%20Price%2CHugh%20Langley%2CSydney%20Bradley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-workers-pushed-limits-of-perks-benefits-pampering-over-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Unacceptable'%3A%20Chinese%20envoy%20calls%20out%20Pakistan%20over%202%20terror%20attacks%20in%206%20months%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A173027