w.nytimes.com%2F2009%2F10%2F11%2Farts%2Ftelevision%2F11cara.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20Cannon%20was%20due%20to%20release%20an%20album%20with%20Island%20Def%20Jam%2C%20Carey's%20label%20at%20the%20time.%20That%20album%20never%20materialized%2C%20and%20Cannon%20told%20Daniels%20he%20was%20worried%20the%20label%20was%20only%20interested%20in%20him%20because%20of%20his%20wife's%20massive%20sales.%20He%20even%20said%20that%20at%20one%20point%20during%20their%20relationship%2C%20he%20would%20wear%20suits%20every%20day%2C%20%26quot%3Btrying%20to%20prove%20that%20I'm%20a%20man.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20thing%2C%20when%20someone%20has%20their%20own%20world%2C%20their%20own%20scope%2C%20their%20own%20bubble%2C%20and%20you%20gotta%20be%20a%20participant%20in%20that%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20%5Bthe%5D%20main%20character!%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mariah%20Carey%20performs%20on%20September%2020%2C%202024%20in%20Sao%20Paulo%2C%20Brazil.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672149e301ea6d83dee4edb0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMariah%20Carey%20performs%20on%20September%2020%2C%202024%20in%20Sao%20Paulo%2C%20Brazil.%3Cp%3EMauricio%20Santana%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20getting%20mad%20at%20myself.%20It%20was%20like%20muscle%20atrophy%2C%26quot%3B%20Cannon%20continued.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20being%20the%20dude%20that%20God%20put%20me%20on%20this%20earth%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECannon%20is%20far%20from%20the%20only%20man%20who's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhusband-jealous-made-more-money-breadwinner-relationship-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadmitted%20to%20being%20jealous%20of%20his%20wife's%20financial%20status%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20%26quot%3BThe%20Love%20Gap%26quot%3B%20by%20journalist%20Jenna%20Birch%2C%20there%20is%20a%20modern%20trend%20of%20straight%20men%20who%20claim%20to%20want%20partners%20who%20are%20intelligent%2C%20ambitious%2C%20and%20successful%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdating-successful-women-makes-many-men-uneasy-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyet%20decline%20to%20pursue%20women%20who%20demonstrate%20those%20qualities%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Love%20Gap%26quot%3B%20cites%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpubmed%2F26302755%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2015%20study%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Personality%20and%20Social%20Psychology%20Bulletin%2C%20which%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bmen%20rated%20women%20who%20were%20supposedly%20more%20intelligent%20as%20more%20desirable%20%E2%80%94%20except%20when%20they%20met%20the%20women%20face-to-face.%20Then%20they%20rated%20the%20women%20as%20less%20desirable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apa.org%2Fpubs%2Fjournals%2Freleases%2Fpsp-a0033769.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2013%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20the%20American%20Psychological%20Association%20found%20a%20similar%20trend%20among%20straight%20men.%20Researchers%20found%20that%20male%20self-esteem%20took%20a%20hit%20when%20a%20female%20partner%20excelled%20in%20a%20task%2C%20while%20women's%20self-esteem%20didn't%20appear%20affected%20by%20their%20male%20partners'%20successes%20or%20failures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20sense%20that%20a%20man%20might%20feel%20threatened%20if%20his%20girlfriend%20outperforms%20him%20in%20something%20they're%20doing%20together%2C%20such%20as%20trying%20to%20lose%20weight%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apa.org%2Fnews%2Fpress%2Freleases%2F2013%2F08%2Fmen-self-esteem%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%259CIt%2520makes%2520sense%2520that%2520a%2C896%2520people%2520in%2520five%2520experiments.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20the%20study's%20lead%20author%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Kate%20Ratliff%2C%20Ph.D.%2C%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Florida.%20%26quot%3BBut%20this%20research%20found%20evidence%20that%20men%20automatically%20interpret%20a%20partner's%20success%20as%20their%20own%20failure%2C%20even%20when%20they're%20not%20in%20direct%20competition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnick-cannon-mariah-carey-marriage-insecurities-money-gender-roles-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730236362000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672111db01ea6d83dee4c6b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnick-cannon-mariah-carey-marriage-insecurities-money-gender-roles-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nick%20Cannon%20recently%20opened%20up%20about%20his%20six-year%20marriage%20to%20Mariah%20Carey%20and%20how%20their%20income%20gap%20made%20him%20question%20his%20role%20as%20a%20man.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cahlgrim%40insider.com%20(Callie%20Ahlgrim)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A244%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnick-cannon-mariah-carey-marriage-insecurities-money-gender-roles-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Life%20sentence%20for%20man%20who%20attacked%20Nancy%20Pelosi%E2%80%99s%20husband%20in%20violent%20home%20invasion%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730235759000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-114747203%2Cimgsize-1188335.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Flife-sentence-for-man-who-attacked-nancy-pelosis-husband-in-violent-home-invasion%2Farticleshow